### Other Agents (Cursor, etc.)

Read the workflow definition at `.windsurf/workflows/<name>.md` and execute the steps described there manually.

### MCP Server (Universal)

All workflows are also available as MCP tools via the workflow server. This works in any editor that supports MCP (Windsurf, Devin, Cursor, etc.):

**Config (`.devin/config.json` or equivalent MCP config):**

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "workflows": {
      "command": "node",
      "args": [".windsurf/tools/workflow-server.js"]
    }
  }
}
```

The MCP server exposes each workflow as a callable tool. When invoked, it returns the full workflow instructions for the agent to execute step by step.

### Workflow API (Config Server)

When the config server is running (`node .windsurf/tools/config-server.js`), workflows are also available via HTTP:

| Endpoint | Method | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `/workflows` | GET | List all available workflows with Devin skill status |
| `/workflow/<name>` | GET | Get full workflow content + Devin skill instructions |
